doc_summary_long: Major parties running in Argentina's midterm congressional election on Sunday have suspended their campaigns after a body, thought to be that a young protester who went missing more than two months ago, was found in a river. A government spokeswoman said President Mauricio Macri's Cambiemos (Let's Change) coalition would halt campaigning for the rest of the day after investigators on Tuesday discovered the body in the Chubut river in the country's southern Patagonia region. Santiago Maldonado: missing backpacker takes center stage in Argentina's elections.
doc_summary_short: Major parties running in Argentina's midterm congressional election on Sunday have suspended their campaigns after a body, thought to be that a young protester who went missing more than two months ago, was found in a river.
doc_title: Argentina halts election campaign after body, thought to be missing activist, found
